Business Brief -- Autodie Corp.:
   `Mass Layoff' May Result
   From Loss of $4.6 Million
Autodie posted a loss of $4.6 million, or 87 cents a
share, for the Nov. 30 quarter. That compares with a loss of
$283,169, or five cents a share, a year earlier. Sales fell
to $9.9 million from $23.5 million.
   About 350 salaried and hourly workers are employed at
Autodie's headquarters and its one plant. An Autodie company
spokesman declined to say how many workers would be affected.
Autodie makes large-scale tools, dies and molds primarily for
the automotive industry. So far, Autodie said the possible
employee cutbacks won't affect its Autobond unit.